The paper is about cross-domain recommendation, which is a subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR). The proposed method involves deep learning, which is a popular topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The method also deals with rating matrices, which are commonly used in collaborative filtering and matrix factorization techniques in recommender systems (cs.CL). Finally, the paper mentions the use of images and review texts as auxiliary information, which are often processed using computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) techniques.
